    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1892-01-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1892-01-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="202" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d202">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Sir
                                    <persName type="to">Julian Pauncefote</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1892-01-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 7,
                                1892</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your note of the 5th instant,
                            in reference to the case of John Gibbons and family, declared to be
                            assisted immigrants likely to become public charges, I have the honor to
                            inform you that prior to the receipt of your note the Commissioner of
                            Immigration at New York had been instructed by telegraph, at the
                            instance of the British Consul-General at New York, to detain the
                            immigrants for a further investigation of the matter.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
